                  "title": "The Huntington by Base Design"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "section-2",
      "title": "Landmark LAB Renovation and 2026 Exhibition Lineup",
      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "id": "para-2-0",
          "content": "The LAB project modernizes the 1919 Myron Hunt building into collaborative spaces with an expanded 8,000-square-foot conservation studio and science history gallery. Lawrence described it as \"the most ambitious building project in The Huntington’s history,\" ensuring researcher access during construction. Design experts praise the rebrand's calibration for clarifying the institution's quiet extraordinariness without overhauling its core.",
          "citations": [
            {
              "primarySource": {
                "id": "source-9",
                "name": "enfilade18thc",
                "url": "https://enfilade18thc.com/2025/07/06/renovations-at-the-huntington-library-to-begin-in-2026/",
                "favicon": "https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=enfilade18thc.com&sz=32",
                "title": "The Huntington by Base Design"
              },
              "additionalCount": 1,
              "additionalSources": [
                {
                  "id": "source-10",
                  "name": "huntington",
                  "url": "https://www.huntington.org",
                  "favicon": "https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=www.huntington.org&sz=32",
                  "title": "The Huntington by Base Design"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "para-2-1",
          "content": "Upcoming shows like \"the eight directions of the wind\" by Edmund de Waal span gardens and galleries through October 2026, exploring idea transmission. Mercedes Dorame's \"Deliquescence\" debuts in March 2026, highlighting Tongva preservation themes, alongside \"This Land Is …\" for the U.S. 250th anniversary. These initiatives signal strong donor support and long-term stewardship for global audiences.",
          "citations": []
        }
      ]
    }
